  "text": "Image: One More Level/505 GamesAlice Jovanée (she/her) is a commerce writer, and she has been writing about gaming and tech since 2005. Prior to Polygon, she worked at publications such as The Verge.If you just can’t get enough of the cyberpunk vibe, Humble is currently offering a bundle of eight Steam Deck-verified titles for just $14. The highlight of the Humble’s Neon Lights bundle is the fast and brutal cyberpunk platformer Ghostrunner. While the difficulty curve of Ghostrunner can be unforgiving at times, I can’t think of a game that better encapsulates the wall-running cyborg-ninja fantasy.If you’d prefer something a little more chill, I’d definitely recommend checking out some of the adventure titles on this list like The Red Strings Club, ANNO: Mutationem, and Neon Blood. Some other games featured in this bundle include the turn-based strategy title Showgunners, roguelikes Neon Abyss and Black Future ’88, and the Jet Set Radio-inspired RKGK/Rakugaki.As with other Humble bundles, a portion of each sale goes to benefit a nonprofit. In this case, it’s Xperience Studios, a Black-led charity which provides funding for entrepreneurs in the video game industry. You can use the “Adjust Donation” drop-down menu on the right side of the bundle page to adjust how the funds from your sale are distributed.ShopkeeperPolygon’s handpicked deals on games, movies, books, and more.",
